<p>Some important notes:</p>

<ul>
  <li>The output range is defined not by two, but by one iterator pointing at the first element of the output range. Donâ€™t forget the output range has to be at least as big as the input one. If not, the behaviour is <a href="http://sandordargo.com/blog/2019/12/18/stl-alogorithms-tutorial-part-8-transform-non-matching-sizes">undefined</a>.</li>
  <li>Not only the replaced elements are written to the output range, but every element. If you want to copy only replaced items, you have to combine two algorithms. One possibility is this:</li>
</ul>

