<h2 id="replace_if"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">replace_if</code></h2>

<p>Just like <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">replace</code>, <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">replace_if</code> also takes a range defined by the iterators pointing at the first and last elements of it, then right after the range and before the new value instead of an old value it takes a unary predicate.</p>

<p>This result of predicate decides whether a value should be replaced or not. As usual, it can be a pointer to a function, a functor or a <a href="">lambda exprssion</a>.</p>

<p>Here is an example:</p>

<div class="language-cpp highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code><table class="rouge-table"><tbody><tr><td class="rouge-gutter gl"><pre class="lineno">1
