<h2 id="conclusion">Conclusion</h2>

<p>Today, we had a peek into the algorithms replacing elements of a container. We saw that there 4 different versions depending on whether we want an in-place or a copy replace and whether we want to identify to-be-replaced elements by value or by a more elaborate condition.</p>

<p>We also saw that the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">replace*</code> algorithms can only replace all the items matching the condition, in order to replace a given number of items, other algorithms have to be used - a topic for another blog post.</p>

<p>Next time weâ€™ll learn about the fill and generate algorithms. Stay tuned!</p>
